      "id": "GENUS_WALLABIA",
      "name": "Wallabia",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "A monotypic genus containing the Swamp Wallaby — the most genetically distinct of all macropods. Unlike every other member of the family, it does not share the standard macropod chromosome number, a distinction so dramatic that it cannot hybridise with any close relative. It has also been observed to begin a second pregnancy while still gestating the first.",
      "lineage": "Wallabies",
